<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="267" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Lieutenant General <persName type="from">Alvan C.
                                    Gillem, Jr.</persName>, to Colonel <persName type="to">J. Hart
                                    Caughey</persName> at Yenan</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-24">24 March 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>359. Good work. General Chang agrees to 3-paragraph directive that he and
                            General Chou had prepared and discussed previously.<note n="43" xml:id="d267fn43">See draft prepared by General Chou En-lai, <ref target="#pg_564">p. 564</ref>.</note> General Chang also agrees
                            to the inclusion of the words “and fair” in paragraph 3. Inform General
                            Chou that I am presenting General Chang with the memorandum reference
                            Canton and Hankow.<note n="44" xml:id="d267fn44">March 24, <ref target="#pg_617">p. 617</ref>.</note> Team has returned to
                            Hankow area.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>